-- Two U.K. Men Charged With Endangering Pakistan Airways Flight
-- B y   L i n d s a y   F o r t a d o
-- 2013-05-26T12:14:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-26/two-u-k-men-charged-with-endangering-pakistan-airways-flight.html
Two men from Lancashire,  England ,
were charged with endangering an aircraft after a U.K.-bound
Pakistan International Airlines Corp. jet was diverted to London
Stansted airport on Friday, police said.  Taxi driver Tayyab Subhani, 30, and Mohammed Safdar, 41, a
restaurant worker, are being held in police custody until they
appear at a criminal court in Chelmsford, England, tomorrow,
Essex police spokeswoman Emma Thomas said in an e-mailed
statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lindsay Fortado in London at 
